  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Corporate Secretarial Associate",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company: Cypress Singapore PAC</strong></p><p><strong>Cypress Policy of Trust & Empowerment allows flexible working arrangements that allows lifestyle choices and managing childcare or eldercare needs. Workloads will be allocated taking into consideration of each candidates’ situation.</strong></p><p>Job Title: Corporate Secretarial Associate</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p>We are looking for a highly motivated individual with proven track record of Corporate Secretarial experiences to join our team of Corporate Secretarial Professionals</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>You will be assisting the Assistant Manager in corporate secretarial and admin work, which includes:</p><p>° Preparation of Directors’ and Shareholders’ Resolutions and Statutory Returns</p><p>° Prepare accounts in XBRL & submission</p><p>° Ensure compliance with statutory and regulatory requirements (including deadlines)</p><p>° Handle all statutory filings with ACRA, MOM, IRAS and other regional/local  government bodies</p><p>° General administration work, including filing and arranging appointments</p><p>° Maintain a good working relationship with clients and manage their expectations</p><p>° Other ad-hoc duties as and when required</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>° Bachelor's in Accounting or Law or equivalent</p><p>° At least 3 years of relevant experience in a professional firm</p><p>° Strong interpersonal, communication and written skills</p><p>° An eye for detail and deadline-oriented</p><p>° Able to work independently</p><p>° Accountability, a proactive approach, and a positive work attitude.</p>",
